e993bed" class="r-1tl5g15 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Nitric oxide boosts blood flow by relaxing and widening your blood vessels. That means more energy, better endurance, improved heart health — and even enhanced sexual performance. As we age, our body naturally produces less nitric oxide, so replenishing it can help you feel your best again.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="a297e356-1cc6-4371-9005-4bff298ab3df" class="r-1imkbsx" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="b74f21c4-ecae-49da-8225-577a8ce868b3" class="r-guj0sx" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="f7bc21d9-c0ce-4c07-beb3-ca0a3ddca16f" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R5rb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-1xycltk"><div data-rid="b85b3094-542d-4097-842e-63580a502ba9" class="r-d1f49i alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>How long do I need to take Berkeley Life before I see results?</p><p>                    </p></span></div><div data-rid="10486fa9-f9cf-407f-8a34-528d710e038d" class="r-9nfm5u" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:auto;max-height:100%" class="r-18jyc7k" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R5rb2:"><div data-rid="0d4b61f9-4e7e-42c6-b88f-62ac8710a55b" class="r-1sov3ga"><div data-rid="9ca2f203-0e1d-4a54-82f7-7879140b7eba" class="r-142vlay alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Many customers feel the difference within days — more energy, better workouts, improved stamina. For others, it can take a few weeks. The good news? You don’t have to guess. Our Nitric Oxide Test Strips let you <em>see</em> the supplement working within just 90 minutes of taking it.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="46b6baf2-b774-4fa2-87d2-480097a5bb9f" class="r-agtvpw" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="7fdd762c-591b-439d-90e7-f005ad195ad4" class="r-1g61phx" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="87898564-b9ef-4b18-94e2-ba8bc690dd5c" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R6bb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-5kl7w8"><div data-rid="a8813868-b27c-4faf-bc5f-b80e50e8db99" class="r-mwzc4l alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Can I take Berkeley Life with other medications?<br></p></span></div><div data-rid="348c86f0-fb1a-45d6-8dff-675cced77aff" class="r-h0h173" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:auto;max-height:100%" class="r-1xukf8u" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R6bb2:"><div data-rid="09a9c518-5ca5-4960-b970-f5334a27fd14" class="r-13cvw9s"><div data-rid="fbcde08d-f2a0-4639-98ae-680c9536517f" class="r-103v1yv alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Yes. Berkeley Life is safe, well tolerated, and has no known interactions with medications. Still, if you're on a specific treatment plan, it's always smart to check with your doctor.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="6e48be7a-0fd4-4890-aab7-a5c6c28c725b" class="r-1p9szaz" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="64e89fe9-d626-4820-ad2d-28490ba50138" class="r-1hsztst" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="cfc1684f-f21a-4b82-a87c-818da6a8c129" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R6rb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-1m8khrg"><div data-rid="f5a29385-3d44-40fe-9043-0c2684ed0b70" class="r-17dffsb alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Is this product safe? Are there any side effects?</p></span></div><div data-rid="1b303c5f-30cb-4e54-a2f5-54e2efa516a6" class="r-14a8rc1" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:auto;max-height:100%" class="r-18x4wdb" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R6rb2:"><div data-rid="a41fcb2a-9fb2-428e-986e-67a53f6a36fd" class="r-1i0x3sr"><div data-rid="b527f43b-b502-4d80-9fc9-3d549f7b651f" class="r-1lslfm3 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Berkeley Life’s Nitric Oxide Foundation is clinically tested and drug free. It’s generally well-tolerated, but as with any supplement, consult your healthcare provider if you have concerns.</p></span></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="624894ae-269c-4d96-b4bf-1946fc84f4cf" class="r-asf30s" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="dca96de7-6ed9-4883-95a9-8bc19ba31011" class="r-zogybg" data-replo-collapsible="true" data-state="closed" data-orientation="vertical"><div data-rid="a68aa2a8-737b-4512-9af3-8b0d101a0cd5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="replo-:R7bb2:" tabindex="0" role="button" class="r-a0hv7e"><div data-rid="9abeea08-923a-409c-b61b-f9fb78fdeec7" class="r-18g3yz alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Can I get the dietary nitrates in Berkeley Life just through my diet?</p></span></div><div data-rid="db3fce72-e178-4f82-9237-8946d1c191c9" class="r-6h170w" aria-hidden="true"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Collapse/Expand" style="width:var(--rsw, 100%);height:auto;max-height:100%" class="r-15hyz6u" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708"></path></svg></div></div><div hidden="" id="replo-:R7bb2:"><div data-rid="d8822b9a-9d63-4767-9ae4-78b2be8ddf36" class="r-qcd4p4"><div data-rid="8edd31d7-f4b8-47ae-8021-a054781b5b88" class="r-l61o61 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><span style="color: rgb(9, 9, 9)">Leafy greens, beetroot, arugula, spinach and celery are all vegetables known to be high in dietary nitrates. However, nutrient density of the soil across the country makes it difficult to predict exactly how much of these greens are required daily to provide a clinically effective dose of nitrates to produce nitric oxide. In our experience, it requires more leafy greens than most people over 35 are willing or able to consume every day.</span></p></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="5d354321-f97d-439f-b0c1-3484a931805e" data-alchemy-url-hashmark="hcp-reviews" tabindex="-1" id="hcp-reviews" data-alchemy-url-hashmark-ignore="true" class="r-2uzvvm"><div data-rid="64881d14-c625-4154-947e-2a83fc3ec60c" class="r-fikwv4 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Trusted by Experts. Recommended by Practitioners.</p></span></div><div data-rid="cfe5717c-e514-4104-8592-b512bea681c1" class="r-1xy30kq" id="replo-carousel::Rjj2:" role="region" aria-label="Carousel" data-replo-carousel="true"><div data-rid="fdc15792-1e83-486d-afb2-9849ba75666e" class="r-1um093"><div data-replo-component-root="carousel" data-replo-part="slides" data-replo-root-id="replo-carousel:Rdjj2:" data-orientation="horizontal" data-active-slide-position="start" role="region" aria-label="Carousel slides" dir="ltr" style="padding-left:0;padding-right:0;width:100%;height:100%;overflow:visible;position:relative" id="replo-carousel:Rdjj2::track"><div data-replo-component-root="car